# Repository config globs

Repository globs from config should expand a leading `~` and stack with globs
supplied on the command line, so both sources can surface repo-backed picker
entries.

    :bins jj

> [!NOTE]
> 'jj' is available.

    :copy tests/fixtures/jjconfig.toml .jjconfig.toml (copied)

    :t rename-session -t 0 runner (success)
    :$ jj git init config-repo (exit: 0)
    :$ jj describe -R config-repo -m "config glob commit" (exit: 0)
    :$ jj git init cli-repo (exit: 0)
    :$ jj describe -R cli-repo -m "cli glob commit" (exit: 0)

    :w .config/sesh/sesh.toml (written)

```toml
[repo]
globs = ["~/config-repo"]
```

Launch `sesh` with an additional quoted CLI glob, then verify each repository
can be selected from the same picker. Quoting keeps the shell from expanding
its tilde before `sesh` receives it.

    :t new-session -d -s ui "sesh -r '~/cli-repo'" (success)
    :t resize-window -t ui:0 -x 120 -y 10 (success)
    :pane ui:0.0
    :settle (settled)

The config-supplied glob discovers `config-repo` after expanding `~` to the
test user's home directory.

    :k config
    :snap "/\d{4}-\d{2}-\d{2} \d{2}:\d{2}:\d{1,2}/t" "/(?:@|○|◆)\s+([a-z]{8})/w" "/\b([0-9a-f]{8})\b/h"

```terminal
session: config
  1/4 | [C-r] repo: none
▌  config-repo                              ~/config-repo                                                              ┃
────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
@  wwwwwwww (no email set) ttttttttttttttttttt hhhhhhhh
│  (empty) config glob commit
◆  wwwwwwww root() hhhhhhhh



```

The CLI-supplied glob also discovers `cli-repo` after expanding `~`.

    :k C-u cli
    :snap "/\d{4}-\d{2}-\d{2} \d{2}:\d{2}:\d{1,2}/t" "/(?:@|○|◆)\s+([a-z]{8})/w" "/\b([0-9a-f]{8})\b/h"

```terminal
session: cli
  1/4 | [C-r] repo: none
▌  cli-repo                                 ~/cli-repo                                                                 ┃
────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
@  wwwwwwww (no email set) ttttttttttttttttttt hhhhhhhh
│  (empty) cli glob commit
◆  wwwwwwww root() hhhhhhhh



```

